# CPL Server Plugin

This plugin provides server-side API for the TiddlyWiki CPL (Community Plugin Library).

## Features

- **Download Statistics**: Track plugin download counts with IP-based rate limiting
- **Rating System**: Allow users to rate plugins (1-5 stars) with IP-based vote limiting
- **Changelog API**: Serve plugin changelogs

## API Endpoints

### POST /cpl/api/download/:pluginTitle
Record a plugin download. Limited to one count per IP per hour.

### GET /cpl/api/stats/:pluginTitle
Get plugin statistics (download count, rating).

### POST /cpl/api/rate/:pluginTitle
Submit a rating. Body: `{ rating: number(1-5) }`

### GET /cpl/api/changelog/:pluginTitle
Get plugin changelog content.

## Configuration

The plugin stores data in the `data/` directory:
- `data/stats.json` - Download statistics
- `data/ratings.json` - User ratings

## Security

- IP-based rate limiting prevents abuse
- Read-only mode compatible (use with `--listen writers=(anon)`)
- Data files should be backed up regularly
